---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Pre-Construction Termite Barrier Darwin | AS 3660.1 + Form 16 | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Pre-construction AS 3660.1 termite barriers for new builds across Greater Darwin — chemical reticulation, physical barrier (Kordon, HomeGuard), hybrid baiting. Form 16 Termite Management Certificate for the builder's Form 21 handover.">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://darwintermitebarriers.com.au/services/post-construction-protection/">
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">AS 3660.1 pre-construction &middot; Form 16 certified</span>
      <h1>Pre-construction termite barriers across <span class="accent">Greater Darwin</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        New build or major renovation? The NT Building Regulations adopt the
        National Construction Code which makes AS 3660.1 termite-management
        compliance mandatory on every Class 1 (dwelling) and Class 10
        (outbuilding). Without the Form 16 Termite Management Certificate, the
        certifier won&rsquo;t issue Form 21 occupation. We do the chemical
        reticulation, physical-barrier install, or hybrid baiting at
        pre-pour stage, and issue the Form 16 paperwork at handover.
        $2,200&ndash;$4,200 typical Class 1 build.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book an inspection</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Three AS 3660.1 barrier types &mdash; which we use when.</h2>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">

        <h3>1. Chemical reticulation + perimeter (most common).</h3>
        <p>
          Flexible polyethylene reticulation tube installed under the slab and
          around the perimeter at pre-pour stage. Emitters along the tube
          deliver Termidor SC or Premise 200SC into the soil around the slab.
          The tube stays in place permanently and can be re-injected at
          8&ndash;10 year intervals to refresh the barrier. Best long-term
          economy &mdash; renewal is hand-pump injection at the tube end-cap
          rather than re-digging the perimeter. ~$2,200&ndash;$3,600 for a
          standard Class 1.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">2. Physical barrier (Kordon, HomeGuard, Termimesh).</h3>
        <p>
          Termite-impervious sheet material at slab penetrations (pipes,
          electrical, perimeter joints). Doesn&rsquo;t expire &mdash; lifespan
          equals the building. Failures come from builder install errors:
          missed gaps at conduit penetrations, mortar bridging at brick
          ground-courses, displacement during slab pour. We install the
          physical barrier OURSELVES (not the builder) and document with
          photos for the Form 16. ~$2,800&ndash;$4,500 for a standard Class 1.
          Common choice in newer Palmerston estates (Zuccoli, Mitchell).
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">3. Hybrid: chemical perimeter + baiting (rural acreage).</h3>
        <p>
          On Litchfield Council blocks where Mastotermes pressure is high,
          chemical perimeter alone is not enough. We install a chemical-soil
          band around the slab AT pre-pour stage, plus a baiting system
          (Sentricon Always Active stations at 10&ndash;15m intervals) around
          the perimeter and along bushland fence lines. The chemical band
          buys construction-phase protection; the baiting system eliminates
          source colonies long-term. ~$5,500&ndash;$9,500 for a standard rural
          Class 1 with house + shed.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">The Form 16 + builder paperwork chain.</h3>
        <p>
          AS 3660.1 compliance is enforced through documentation. The chain:
        </p>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Pre-pour inspection</strong> &mdash; we attend site before slab pour to confirm reticulation / physical barrier install.</li>
          <li><strong>Post-pour inspection</strong> &mdash; verify nothing was damaged during slab pour, confirm soil treatment perimeter applied.</li>
          <li><strong>Form 16 Termite Management Certificate</strong> &mdash; issued by us, lists the barrier type, chemicals used, lifespan, expected next-inspection date.</li>
          <li><strong>Builder lodges Form 16 + other Form 16s</strong> with the certifier as part of the Form 21 occupation certificate package.</li>
          <li><strong>Certifier issues Form 21</strong> &mdash; occupation legal.</li>
        </ol>
        <p>
          Missing the Form 16 stops the entire handover. We&rsquo;ve been called
          in late on multiple builds where the original pest contractor went
          out of business mid-build and the Form 16 was missing. Retrofitting
          a Form 16 requires destructive testing at perimeter sample points
          &mdash; expensive and slow. Engaging us at pre-pour is much cheaper.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Renovations + extensions.</h3>
        <p>
          Renovations that disturb the slab perimeter, slab penetrations, or
          the existing chemical-band layout require reinstatement of the
          AS 3660 barrier under AS 3660.2. New bathroom slab cuts, kitchen
          plumbing reroutes, deck additions, ground-floor extensions &mdash;
          all require a fresh Form 16 paperwork trail covering the disturbed
          zone. We can reinstate as a focused job (~$1,500&ndash;$3,500) or
          full perimeter renewal if the existing barrier is also expired.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Where we work.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/palmerston/">Palmerston</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/casuarina/">Casuarina</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/nightcliff/">Nightcliff</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/humpty-doo/">Humpty Doo</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/howard-springs/">Howard Springs</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/greater-darwin/">All Greater Darwin</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free pre-construction barrier quote.</h2>
        <p>New build, major renovation or post-renovation reinstatement. Form 16 included. Free site quote.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
